claim.claim-text:
1. A quick manhole/handhole construction method and a plurality of related devices that at least comprise a cutting unit, which comprises: 
a radial feeding device composed of a pneumatic motor and a screw feeding mechanism; 
a cutting plate which is a circular blade unit covered by a shelter having a placing prop fastened at a proper position of a exterior; 
a chassis whereon a fixing holder is set, and a column casing is appended at an appropriate position of periphery, and a steering gear mechanism is set at a top of said column casing, and a shaft is extended downward from said steering gear mechanism, and a planet gear is fastened on said shaft; 
a base whereof a fixed gear is fastened on upper surface of said base and at least three extending arms, which can be adjusted and controlled by a nut, are set at a bottom face continuously with dividing area of the bottom face with equal parts; 
a vessel which is connected with a duct and is able to placed into said placing prop on said shelter; 
wherein said shelter of said cutting plate and said radial feeding device are fastened to said fixing holder of said chassis, and said blade of said cutting plate is fastened to said pneumatic motor of said radial feeding device, and said chassis is set at the top of said base, and makes said planet gear set on said chassis can engage with said fixed gear set on said base.

2. A quick manhole/handhole construction method and a plurality of related devices as recited in claim 1, wherein said device at least comprises a lifter, which further comprises: 
a frame, whereon a plurality of symmetrical position holes locate at suitable positions; 
a pair of fastened wheels containing two wheels, which are respectively set at both sides of one end of said frame; 
a pair of mobile wheels containing two wheels, which respectively is appended with a mobile link, which is joined at two sides of said frame; 
a hook module, wherein the main part is a stick with a pair of sleeves, which have a pair of positioning holes, can slide on said frame, and respectively set at two ends, and a pair of mobile sleeves, which respectively has a hook at a bottom and a plurality of poisoning holes at a top, is set at a middle; 
a plurality of the positioning pins for fastening the hook set; 
a pair of folding unit, which comprises a pair of foldable links respectively, and a string; 
a stopping unit, which comprises at least a stopping plate, which is fixed at a suitable position of said frame such that said frame can be avoided from contacting ground when said frame is horizontally placed down; 
wherein said pair of fastened wheels are respectively set at two sides of one end of said frame, and correspond to said pair of mobile wheels, and said pair of folding units are used to link said fastened wheels and said mobile wheels, and said pair of folding units are connected by a string passing through said frame such that when said string is pulled, said pair of fastened wheels and said pair of mobile wheels can be pulled by said pair of folding units and said foldable links between wheels can be folded; and 
wherein said positioning pins of said pair of positioning pins can simultaneously pass through the poisoning holes of said hook module and said frame such that quick position of said mobile hooks can be done.

4. A quick manhole/handhole construction method and a plurality of related devices as recited in claim 1, wherein said construction method at least comprises a set of steps as follows: 
Step1 Using said lifter to lift and move a manhole/handhole; 
Step2 Placing and positioning said cutting unit into said manhole/handhole, and using said cutting unit to cut a surface of an asphalt road above the manhole/handhole; 
Step3 Placing and positioning said cutting unit into a culvert, and using said cutting unit to cut said culvert connected to a bottom of said manhole/handhole; 
Step4 Hanging away said manhole/handhole; 
Step5 Placing a new manhole/handhole; 
Step6 Using said lifter to move and cover said manhole/handhole cover; 
Step7 Laying said surface of said asphalt road above said manhole/handhole.
